snippet.textDisplay: Honestly the movie ended pretty okay, considering how mismatched (mediocre) the whole series was. Some parts didn’t make sense. They kind of treat c3po like trash. In the original series they were a bit annoyed, but Luke and the others still cared and acted humanely. This time they were just forceful getting c3po to reset his memory. Plot holes everywhere. The smooch at the end. Well, it ended pretty good for how messy the series was. It actually could have been worse. It started off pretty Bad though. It was like a fan fiction. snippet.textDisplay:
Looks like I'm the only fan here ... if you were there in '77 ... you NEED fan service. I hate being pigeon-holed. I hated TFA. I hated TLJ. I liked TROS. I cried at the end.
Millennials hate everything. They hated the prequels and cried 'Meh!' to the point where GL sold the franchise. It's the 'fans' fault. To me, the real fans are those people who have been on this ride since the OT. We have more invested in it and the opinions of those who haven't invested more than 40 years in the saga fall from their mouths like turds.
I really hate the millennial critics, they just don't know how to enjoy. I cried at the end of TROS, I had waited 42 years to see that and it was great - fan service? Absolutely. Us longstanding fans - not the recent whiny generation - we deserve that fan service thank you. These critics with their webcams who never created art in their lives and all they can to is be a critic, there's no skill or value in it. They're empty. It's sad. It seems to be all younger fans that weren't here in '77 who don't like this movie. I loved it. I can't understand 'fans' who are talking about not going to see it. I waited 42 years for this and I loved it - I hated TLJ and TFA - but I loved the ending and cried after the last scene. The saga is complete, and Abrams did quite a good job given what he had to work with after 8 I thought.

snippet.textDisplay: Phantom Menace has Qui Gon Jin, Darth Maul, you can see "young" Palpatine starting his plotting... it's not a great movie by any means, but it's leagues better than any of the Disney's Trilogy films (I refuse to consider them along the Lucas's trilogys), heck! even prequels look like masterpieces besides any of those DT ones and make Hayden Christiansen look like the perfect mix between Pacino and De Niro compared to Rey or Kylo. Jeez! I'm going to need to binge the mandalorian series three times in a row just to wash the bad taste from my mouth speaking about the Disney Trilogy
